Company A proposes to implement a secure Electronic ID (EID) system based on Distributed Ledger Technology (DLT)/Blockchain for the government project. Key services include seamless DLT/Blockchain integration, secure certificate issuance, decentralized verification, user-friendly interfaces, interoperability with existing systems, compliance with data protection standards, comprehensive training, ongoing support, cost-efficiency, scalability, enhanced security features, and audit trails for accountability. This proposal aims to establish an efficient and tamper-proof EID system, aligning with the government's objectives for certificate issuance and verification while prioritizing security and user experience.
